headline: Return of Venezuelan crude could cut US fuel oil imports
summary: BENGALURU/LONDON Jan 27 (Reuters) - U. demand for imported fuel oil is set to fall this year as refiners snap up new flows of heavy Venezuelan crude, ​yielding more domestically produced fuel oil that can be processed into higher-value products such as gasoline and ‌diesel.
